1
00:00:41,124 --> 00:00:44,461
In-guk! I told you not to play
with slime toys in the morning.

2
00:00:54,137 --> 00:00:56,222
That's the alarm at our house.

3
00:01:03,354 --> 00:01:04,481
For romance,

4
00:01:04,564 --> 00:01:07,025
you'll be carrying Mr. Son's child...

5
00:01:07,108 --> 00:01:08,485
For comedy,

6
00:01:08,651 --> 00:01:12,197
you'll be a gold-digging writer
who seduces Mr. Son to help your career.

7
00:01:15,366 --> 00:01:18,119
Why does a day have to begin
no matter what?

8
00:01:18,661 --> 00:01:21,706
It's a robust system
that never allows a single error.

9
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:24,042
I should sleep some more.

10
00:01:24,250 --> 00:01:28,087
I'll refuse today
by sleeping until tomorrow morning.

11
00:01:38,181 --> 00:01:41,351
Come on out.
I'm really going to hit you today.

12
00:01:41,434 --> 00:01:43,102
I'm going to call the police then.

13
00:01:48,024 --> 00:01:50,568
So my refusal is refused.

14
00:02:00,286 --> 00:02:01,579
Get off of me now.

15
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:04,582
I have a strong personality,
but not a strong physique.

16
00:02:21,182 --> 00:02:22,600
Rice or bread?

17
00:02:25,395 --> 00:02:27,105
Come on. You should eat something.

18
00:02:51,421 --> 00:02:54,591
I have a friend
who's a famous psychologist.

19
00:02:55,425 --> 00:02:56,593
I was frustrated

20
00:02:57,135 --> 00:03:00,013
so I went to talk to her.

21
00:03:00,263 --> 00:03:02,056
People who lost their loved ones

22
00:03:02,140 --> 00:03:04,350
may grieve and suffer
from auditory and visual hallucinations.

23
00:03:04,434 --> 00:03:08,104
A sense of loss is commonly shown
in the process of mourning.

24
00:03:08,354 --> 00:03:09,606
But in most cases,

25
00:03:09,689 --> 00:03:12,191
they get over it in about two months.

26
00:03:13,318 --> 00:03:16,195
What Eun-jeong is going through
is understandable enough,

27
00:03:16,404 --> 00:03:18,656
but such cases are still being
studied in the academic circles.

28
00:03:19,073 --> 00:03:21,618
So an accurate diagnosis
can't be made for now.

29
00:03:21,701 --> 00:03:24,162
Excuse me. Can I take a look
at the 70-200mm lens?

30
00:03:24,245 --> 00:03:25,622
The 70-200mm?

31
00:03:35,048 --> 00:03:36,591
Among us,

32
00:03:36,799 --> 00:03:39,469
it's called persistent complex
bereavement disorder.

33
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:42,972
It means the disorder has continued
for over a year.

34
00:03:43,431 --> 00:03:46,100
The reason they find it
difficult to deal with it

35
00:03:46,434 --> 00:03:47,769
is usually found

36
00:03:47,852 --> 00:03:50,271
in their childhood relationship
with their parents and family.

37
00:03:51,648 --> 00:03:54,442
My family was happy.

38
00:03:55,443 --> 00:03:57,362
Until I confessed about myself.

39
00:04:00,448 --> 00:04:01,866
I guess I could've been a reason.

40
00:04:01,950 --> 00:04:04,244
Hey. Don't.

41
00:04:04,369 --> 00:04:06,579
It's actually because of me

42
00:04:08,122 --> 00:04:09,249
that my parents live abroad.

43
00:04:09,332 --> 00:04:10,333
Hey.

44
00:04:10,625 --> 00:04:13,753
Your mom is a travel writer
and your dad is a photographer.

45
00:04:13,836 --> 00:04:17,090
It's just that traveled around the world
after raising their children.

46
00:04:17,173 --> 00:04:18,675
They found a good place for their old age

47
00:04:18,758 --> 00:04:20,677
and settled down there happily.

48
00:04:21,678 --> 00:04:23,429
Don't you dare undermine their coolness.

49
00:04:23,513 --> 00:04:24,514
She's right.

50
00:04:24,681 --> 00:04:26,516
Your parents understood you.

51
00:04:26,599 --> 00:04:28,268
They pretended to understand me.

52
00:04:28,351 --> 00:04:30,270
Otherwise, why would they
not invite me over even once?

53
00:04:32,981 --> 00:04:35,024
Eun-jeong lost her parents because of me.

54
00:04:35,108 --> 00:04:36,526
Hey, pull yourself together.

55
00:04:36,859 --> 00:04:40,238
Why are you being like this? I'm scared.

56
00:04:41,864 --> 00:04:43,116
Am I the only one feeling that way?

57
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:45,618
Am I the only one who's been there?

58
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:54,544
Okay. I'm sorry.

59
00:05:04,929 --> 00:05:08,224
I really want Eun-jeong to see my friend.

60
00:05:10,143 --> 00:05:12,854
And I need you
to come up with a way, Hyo-bong.

61
00:05:17,692 --> 00:05:18,693
Okay.

62
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:25,658
I'm worried.

63
00:05:27,201 --> 00:05:28,328
And I feel bad.

64
00:05:31,122 --> 00:05:32,373
So I want to avoid this.

65
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:35,418
How should I tell her?

66
00:05:37,045 --> 00:05:38,421
Just tell her.

67
00:05:41,799 --> 00:05:43,301
Eun-jeong is smart.

68
00:05:44,177 --> 00:05:45,887
And she loves you a lot.

69
00:05:48,598 --> 00:05:52,185
"My brother must've struggled a lot
to tell me about this."

70
00:05:53,644 --> 00:05:54,812
She would think.

71
00:05:55,772 --> 00:05:57,482
Her heart's already burdened,

72
00:06:01,235 --> 00:06:02,653
and I'm adding more to it.

73
00:06:02,737 --> 00:06:04,363
Let's just think

74
00:06:04,989 --> 00:06:07,158
that we're emptying it out
to fill it up again.

75
00:06:37,814 --> 00:06:38,856
Hello?

76
00:06:39,315 --> 00:06:40,358
Rice with seasoned thistle.

77
00:06:41,192 --> 00:06:43,319
-What?
-Today's menu.

78
00:06:44,028 --> 00:06:45,947
How about rice with seasoned thistle?

79
00:06:47,490 --> 00:06:49,033
I just ate.

80
00:06:49,784 --> 00:06:51,369
Then we can make one
and eat it for dinner.

81
00:06:51,452 --> 00:06:53,246
I'm on my way to your office.

82
00:06:55,581 --> 00:06:57,333
I'm in my office now.

83
00:07:00,628 --> 00:07:02,004
But I'm on my way.

84
00:07:04,048 --> 00:07:06,968
Well... I won't go to my office today.

85
00:07:08,010 --> 00:07:09,178
I have a plan.

86
00:07:10,972 --> 00:07:11,973
You do?

87
00:07:13,141 --> 00:07:14,308
Yes, I'm hanging up.

88
00:08:02,690 --> 00:08:04,484
I didn't know it happened.

89
00:08:05,902 --> 00:08:08,196
So why are you telling me that now?

90
00:08:08,279 --> 00:08:09,447
When should I have told you?

91
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:12,533
You never know
because you're not a housewife.

92
00:08:12,617 --> 00:08:14,118
I'm busy and bored at the same time.

93
00:08:14,535 --> 00:08:16,787
You should tell me right away
when something interesting happens.

94
00:08:16,954 --> 00:08:19,999
Mom, I'm serious.

95
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,251
Hey, it's good though.

96
00:08:22,502 --> 00:08:24,128
I'm happy for Hwan-dong too.

97
00:08:26,047 --> 00:08:29,008
I miss him. You know I liked him.

98
00:08:30,384 --> 00:08:32,261
I'm being serious here.

99
00:08:32,470 --> 00:08:34,222
It's okay. It's nothing serious.

100
00:08:34,305 --> 00:08:36,557
You can't decide if I'm okay or not.

101
00:08:36,641 --> 00:08:39,393
I'm your mom.
I can tell by the way you eat your food.

102
00:08:39,602 --> 00:08:41,854
You're just fine. You're eating very well.

103
00:08:42,396 --> 00:08:43,814
I'm not eating well.

104
00:08:44,065 --> 00:08:45,358
I'm picking on food.

105
00:08:45,441 --> 00:08:47,568
If you wanted to pick on food,
you should've used chopsticks.

106
00:08:47,777 --> 00:08:49,862
You're just scooping food into your mouth.

107
00:08:50,655 --> 00:08:51,697
You're quite keen.

108
00:08:52,073 --> 00:08:54,033
I don't know. I'm hungry
because I'm worried.

109
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:57,370
Aren't you more worried about Mr. Son
than yourself?

110
00:08:57,537 --> 00:08:58,955
Do you like him?

111
00:09:04,418 --> 00:09:05,836
What are you talking about?

112
00:09:06,170 --> 00:09:09,465
Jin-joo, this is my second time
to see it in my life.

113
00:09:09,924 --> 00:09:13,761
I gave birth to you 30 years ago.

114
00:09:13,886 --> 00:09:15,596
Back then, your face was all red.

115
00:09:15,888 --> 00:09:18,432
And now, it is completely red again.

116
00:09:19,725 --> 00:09:22,228
My gosh. I should go tell your dad.

117
00:09:22,687 --> 00:09:25,773
This is not something to tell Dad about.
Do you really have to tell him?

118
00:09:26,524 --> 00:09:28,651
You never know
because you don't run a laundry.

119
00:09:28,734 --> 00:09:30,695
He's busy, but he's bored.

120
00:09:31,445 --> 00:09:33,447
I have to go tell him.

121
00:09:33,531 --> 00:09:36,492
-I'm going to tell him.
-I bit my tongue. That's why I blushed.

122
00:09:36,576 --> 00:09:38,286
Okay. You like the director.

123
00:09:38,369 --> 00:09:39,537
-Hey.
-Honey.

124
00:09:40,830 --> 00:09:42,415
Will you listen to me?

125
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:58,472
Will Mr. Son and Ms. Lim get married?

126
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:05,187
No.

127
00:10:05,688 --> 00:10:07,064
That can't be right.

128
00:10:07,148 --> 00:10:11,027
A lot of rumors in this field
have turned out to be true.

129
00:10:11,193 --> 00:10:13,863
It happens a lot. Aren't I right?

130
00:10:13,946 --> 00:10:15,781
Well... You're right.

131
00:10:15,990 --> 00:10:17,325
They might get married separately.

132
00:10:19,327 --> 00:10:20,911
Sure. I guess that's not true.

133
00:10:22,288 --> 00:10:23,539
I heard she's pregnant.

134
00:10:25,708 --> 00:10:27,668
-Gosh.
-The word is out.

135
00:10:27,752 --> 00:10:29,920
-What?
-They say she's pregnant.

136
00:10:30,504 --> 00:10:31,631
I heard it.

137
00:10:33,174 --> 00:10:34,634
Why do you care so much?

138
00:10:34,842 --> 00:10:35,801
Of course I do.

139
00:10:35,885 --> 00:10:37,720
What does Beom-su mean to you?

140
00:10:38,095 --> 00:10:41,599
A creature that I love the most
but I couldn't have.

141
00:10:42,099 --> 00:10:44,018
What do I mean to you?

142
00:10:45,102 --> 00:10:47,897
A creature that I love the most
and I have.

143
00:10:47,980 --> 00:10:51,108
"And I have?" A creature you have?

144
00:10:51,984 --> 00:10:54,445
-Just how many creatures do you have?
-Nothing else. Just you.

145
00:10:56,822 --> 00:10:57,907
What is this?

146
00:10:58,407 --> 00:11:00,076
It feels good, but it's a little awkward.

147
00:11:00,409 --> 00:11:03,621
It's like I was taking a walk
on a sunny day after a rain,

148
00:11:03,704 --> 00:11:06,082
but I stepped in a puddle.

149
00:11:06,248 --> 00:11:08,250
My socks are all soaked,

150
00:11:08,334 --> 00:11:10,086
but the weather is still sunny.
This is how I feel.

151
00:11:10,169 --> 00:11:11,462
Am I feeling it right?

152
00:11:11,545 --> 00:11:13,714
Is this something
we should be discussing at work?

153
00:11:13,798 --> 00:11:15,966
No. I should get going.

154
00:11:35,986 --> 00:11:38,864
Everyone knows why you look like that,
so change it now.

155
00:11:40,324 --> 00:11:41,325
We need to talk.

156
00:11:43,744 --> 00:11:45,538
-I'm hungry.
-I'll buy you coffee.

157
00:11:46,330 --> 00:11:47,331
What?

158
00:11:57,091 --> 00:11:58,592
That's why she's avoiding me?

159
00:11:58,884 --> 00:12:00,511
The writer is avoiding the director.

160
00:12:00,594 --> 00:12:02,638
This isn't about a writer and a director.

161
00:12:02,805 --> 00:12:06,684
It feels like coed high school
all over again.

162
00:12:07,685 --> 00:12:09,478
I know. It's so childish.

163
00:12:09,562 --> 00:12:11,772
This is such a small industry.

164
00:12:11,939 --> 00:12:14,817
Lee Dong-min and Kim Eun-ha were
a famous couple back in school.

165
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:16,986
And they appeared in my previous work
as a married couple.

166
00:12:17,069 --> 00:12:19,530
Eun-ha's husband is the CEO
of a production company.

167
00:12:19,613 --> 00:12:22,324
And he cast Dong-min
in their upcoming work.

168
00:12:22,408 --> 00:12:23,701
Do you think he tried to kill him?

169
00:12:23,951 --> 00:12:27,288
Even you dated Sol-bi
while working on music for your drama.

170
00:12:28,122 --> 00:12:29,415
Do you think you won't run into her?

171
00:12:29,498 --> 00:12:31,333
You will. So what?

172
00:12:31,417 --> 00:12:34,503
It's just the same for Ms. Lim. It means
you've been in this industry for long.

173
00:12:34,587 --> 00:12:36,172
And it means you're competent.

174
00:12:36,255 --> 00:12:38,924
You're making it sound like
I'm actually dating Ms. Lim.

175
00:12:39,008 --> 00:12:40,301
Why couldn't you be?

176
00:12:40,384 --> 00:12:42,470
Just suit yourself to the rumor.

177
00:12:42,553 --> 00:12:44,096
I can't date someone
because of some rumor.

178
00:12:44,180 --> 00:12:45,556
It's not just a rumor.

179
00:12:45,639 --> 00:12:47,183
You do like Ms. Lim.

180
00:12:47,266 --> 00:12:50,144
Listen. Why are you hiding your feelings?
Why disguise it?

181
00:12:50,227 --> 00:12:51,270
That's it.

182
00:12:51,645 --> 00:12:53,105
Shut your mouth now.

183
00:12:53,689 --> 00:12:56,609
I'm sure you two like each other.

184
00:12:56,692 --> 00:12:58,235
What do you think? Just date her.

185
00:12:58,444 --> 00:13:00,488
Marry her, too. Live happily ever after.

186
00:13:00,571 --> 00:13:01,864
Once one of you dies first,

187
00:13:01,947 --> 00:13:03,115
when those who are spreading

188
00:13:03,199 --> 00:13:06,368
the rumor right now come to the funeral,
it's not like they'd say

189
00:13:06,452 --> 00:13:09,622
"That awkward relationship
of yours is finally over."

190
00:13:10,414 --> 00:13:13,334
People will gossip anyway.
It will just spread around

191
00:13:13,417 --> 00:13:16,212
in this petty small industry
and vanish into vapor.

192
00:13:16,295 --> 00:13:17,838
Do you think I don't know that?

193
00:13:17,922 --> 00:13:19,089
She's a budding writer.

194
00:13:19,173 --> 00:13:21,717
She wouldn't be used
to being gossiped about like this.

195
00:13:21,884 --> 00:13:24,553
See? You're worried about the writer.

196
00:13:24,637 --> 00:13:27,389
-You like her.
-People like you are exaggerating it.

197
00:13:27,473 --> 00:13:30,351
Why do you always have to turn
my consideration into romance?

198
00:13:30,434 --> 00:13:32,311
Since when were you being so considerate?

199
00:13:33,687 --> 00:13:36,106
Forget it. Stop worrying about it

200
00:13:36,482 --> 00:13:37,441
and do what you have to do.

201
00:13:37,525 --> 00:13:39,860
Of course. It's not like
I'll cancel my project because of this.

202
00:13:39,944 --> 00:13:41,612
No, that's not what I mean.

203
00:13:44,448 --> 00:13:46,951
Something you have to do
for someone you like.

204
00:13:47,159 --> 00:13:48,160
Don't you get it?

205
00:13:48,327 --> 00:13:50,287
Seriously, even at your age
you don't get it?

206
00:13:54,291 --> 00:13:56,210
Why are you trying so hard

207
00:13:57,253 --> 00:13:59,213
to make me date someone?

208
00:13:59,505 --> 00:14:01,715
Why are you being
exceptionally passionate?

209
00:14:04,009 --> 00:14:05,511
It's because of Da-mi, right?

210
00:14:18,023 --> 00:14:19,358
I'm on duty right now.

211
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:22,903
I should do my job.

212
00:14:27,157 --> 00:14:30,828
SCENE 56, SO-HEE'S KITCHEN, NIGHT

213
00:14:32,830 --> 00:14:35,416
Don't fix it. Just keep it as it is.

214
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:37,835
Your script was really fun to read.

215
00:14:39,587 --> 00:14:43,340
How did I end up unconsciously
writing down about my past?

216
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:46,927
Am I really fine
with what happened back then?

217
00:14:47,511 --> 00:14:51,223
Was I trying to ask him
if he remembers it too?

218
00:14:51,724 --> 00:14:53,183
Gosh, I don't know.

219
00:14:53,851 --> 00:14:56,437
Whatever it is, it's fine.

220
00:14:56,645 --> 00:14:58,022
There's no reason I can't do this.

221
00:14:58,939 --> 00:14:59,940
Be careful.

222
00:15:00,024 --> 00:15:01,066
I'm scared.

223
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:03,861
-What?
-All right. Don't open your eyes.

224
00:15:04,278 --> 00:15:06,196
-This is scary.
-All right.

225
00:15:07,698 --> 00:15:08,949
We're here.

226
00:15:09,533 --> 00:15:11,535
Open the locker in front of you.

227
00:15:13,203 --> 00:15:14,580
-This one?
-Yes.

228
00:15:14,997 --> 00:15:18,250
What is it? I wonder what it is.

229
00:15:18,584 --> 00:15:20,711
I know what it is. It's a bouquet.

230
00:15:24,340 --> 00:15:26,926
If you were going to get me
something fragrant like this,

231
00:15:27,009 --> 00:15:28,344
you should have covered my nose too.

232
00:15:30,429 --> 00:15:31,764
You're so mean.

233
00:15:32,014 --> 00:15:33,349
Go get a stuffy nose or something.

234
00:15:41,732 --> 00:15:44,568
You... What is this?

235
00:15:44,652 --> 00:15:45,653
Here.

236
00:15:45,903 --> 00:15:46,820
Gosh.

237
00:15:48,864 --> 00:15:51,700
Have you been busy working part-time
to buy me this?

238
00:15:54,286 --> 00:15:56,914
I like flowers. They make me happy enough.

239
00:15:57,373 --> 00:15:58,999
You should be studying.

240
00:15:59,083 --> 00:16:01,335
Gosh, you're giving me a headache.

241
00:16:01,418 --> 00:16:04,004
Go ahead and nag at me. It's just nice.

242
00:16:04,672 --> 00:16:05,965
How much did you pay for this?

243
00:16:06,423 --> 00:16:07,841
I spent all the money I have.

244
00:16:07,925 --> 00:16:10,135
I'm going to earn a lot of money
and give it all to you.

245
00:16:10,219 --> 00:16:12,596
-Why are you so immature?
-At least I'm competent.

246
00:16:13,764 --> 00:16:14,765
I love you.

247
00:16:16,308 --> 00:16:17,851
I've got some scolding to do to you.

248
00:16:18,352 --> 00:16:19,603
But first things first.

249
00:16:22,773 --> 00:16:24,483
I'VE GOT SOME SCOLDING TO DO TO YOU
BUT FIRST THINGS FIRST

250
00:16:24,566 --> 00:16:25,442
This is so lame.

251
00:16:26,068 --> 00:16:27,528
It's just cute.

252
00:16:30,030 --> 00:16:31,115
No, it's lame.

253
00:16:31,198 --> 00:16:33,367
Have you ever done
anything like that though?

254
00:16:34,743 --> 00:16:37,955
You just keep trying
to make me look sad and lonely.

255
00:16:38,038 --> 00:16:40,541
Back in the day, I've done all...

256
00:16:44,211 --> 00:16:45,212
those things.

257
00:16:47,131 --> 00:16:49,550
But why can't I remember anything?

258
00:16:49,633 --> 00:16:51,593
It means you've never done it.

259
00:16:52,970 --> 00:16:56,807
You can't say it happened
unless you remember it.

260
00:16:57,224 --> 00:16:59,268
I think it did happen.

261
00:16:59,810 --> 00:17:01,937
But I'm not sure if it was my experience,

262
00:17:03,814 --> 00:17:07,026
my script or my dream.

263
00:17:10,195 --> 00:17:12,406
What about you?
Have you ever done anything like that?

264
00:17:12,740 --> 00:17:13,949
Do you remember anything?

265
00:17:14,033 --> 00:17:15,034
Yes, I have.

266
00:17:15,993 --> 00:17:17,161
I remember it very clearly.

267
00:17:17,661 --> 00:17:19,329
I just don't want to remember it.

268
00:17:19,413 --> 00:17:21,081
Why not? You said it's cute.

269
00:17:21,165 --> 00:17:23,250
I met my ex-wife when we were young.

270
00:17:23,333 --> 00:17:26,170
And we did all sort of crazy
lovey-dovey stuff.

271
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:29,631
But when we got a divorce, we promised

272
00:17:29,715 --> 00:17:31,967
not talk to each other
unless it's about child support expenses.

273
00:17:32,134 --> 00:17:35,971
It's just strange to think
about the memories of her.

274
00:17:37,973 --> 00:17:39,224
It just feels bitter.

275
00:17:45,606 --> 00:17:47,941
I'm not going to drink
even if you say that.

276
00:17:48,025 --> 00:17:49,068
I have to work.

277
00:17:49,443 --> 00:17:50,944
Let's drink with Beom-su and Ms. Lim.

278
00:17:51,236 --> 00:17:52,654
-What?
-Call her.

279
00:17:52,863 --> 00:17:54,865
-Me?
-You should call Ms. Lim now.

280
00:17:54,948 --> 00:17:56,116
Why would I call her?

281
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:57,451
Let's go to a sashimi restaurant.

282
00:17:57,534 --> 00:17:58,911
You should call her.

283
00:17:58,994 --> 00:18:00,370
-Let's have soju and beer.
-My goodness.

284
00:18:00,454 --> 00:18:01,455
With some sashimi.

285
00:18:02,122 --> 00:18:03,082
Yes, ma'am.

286
00:18:03,165 --> 00:18:05,751
I'll talk to the director
and get back to you.

287
00:18:05,834 --> 00:18:07,419
Okay, thank you.

288
00:18:08,712 --> 00:18:09,963
Jae-hun.

289
00:18:10,047 --> 00:18:12,549
I think we need to pick a casting team
and a casting director.

290
00:18:12,633 --> 00:18:15,010
The one the director used to work with
can't work with us.

291
00:18:17,012 --> 00:18:18,013
Jae-hun.

292
00:18:19,389 --> 00:18:20,766
-Yes?
-Hang on.

293
00:18:20,849 --> 00:18:21,809
Hello, Ms. Hwang.

294
00:18:21,892 --> 00:18:24,478
Hello, Mr. Son. Do you have time to talk?

295
00:18:24,561 --> 00:18:25,687
Yes, go ahead.

296
00:18:27,189 --> 00:18:30,234
I got a call from Jeong So-yeon's agency.

297
00:18:30,692 --> 00:18:32,111
They liked the script,

298
00:18:32,194 --> 00:18:35,114
so they gave it to their actress,
and she's reading it right now.

299
00:18:36,406 --> 00:18:39,118
But as far as I know,

300
00:18:39,201 --> 00:18:41,620
Jeong So-yeon is starting a movie in July.

301
00:18:41,703 --> 00:18:43,288
I don't think she's available.

302
00:18:43,372 --> 00:18:45,290
But the CEO of her agency called me

303
00:18:45,374 --> 00:18:47,251
and said he wants to meet up with you.

304
00:18:47,334 --> 00:18:50,170
I guess he will try to convince me
to cast another actress.

305
00:18:50,712 --> 00:18:51,672
I'll meet him anyway.

306
00:18:51,755 --> 00:18:53,715
Who are the other actresses in the agency?

307
00:19:05,477 --> 00:19:07,855
So So-min's here.

308
00:19:07,938 --> 00:19:08,939
Pardon?

309
00:19:09,940 --> 00:19:12,317
Well... They have Lee So-min.

310
00:19:19,950 --> 00:19:21,410
THINGS WILL BE FINE ONCE YOU TURN THIRTY

311
00:19:21,493 --> 00:19:23,328
I went to the same college
with this writer.

312
00:19:23,412 --> 00:19:25,497
But I've never met her
since I took a year off.

313
00:19:26,415 --> 00:19:27,749
Now we're meeting again like this.

314
00:19:28,542 --> 00:19:30,210
I went to the same college as you,

315
00:19:30,294 --> 00:19:32,588
but I've never seen you
since you took a year off.

316
00:19:33,547 --> 00:19:34,923
And yet we met again like this.

317
00:19:35,007 --> 00:19:36,341
Did you recommend me?

318
00:19:36,425 --> 00:19:37,426
No way.

319
00:19:37,759 --> 00:19:39,261
I happened to meet Director Son,

320
00:19:39,344 --> 00:19:41,263
and I did tell him
that I'm working with you.

321
00:19:41,555 --> 00:19:43,140
But I don't get involved
in personal affairs

322
00:19:43,223 --> 00:19:44,600
of the people whom I work with.

323
00:19:44,683 --> 00:19:46,935
Is that why you gave me
the heads up on Min-jun?

324
00:19:54,902 --> 00:19:56,820
The script is interesting.

325
00:19:57,446 --> 00:19:58,447
But they wouldn't cast me

326
00:19:58,530 --> 00:20:00,032
-as the main character.
-Why not?

327
00:20:00,115 --> 00:20:02,034
They probably wouldn't like me.
I'm not pretty.

328
00:20:02,117 --> 00:20:03,118
You are pretty.

329
00:20:03,368 --> 00:20:06,288
You're the prettiest person I know.

330
00:20:08,081 --> 00:20:09,958
-What are you doing?
-I'm just telling the truth.

331
00:20:10,042 --> 00:20:12,252
This isn't a time I have to flatter you.

332
00:20:13,045 --> 00:20:14,421
You already seem to be in a good mood.

333
00:20:15,380 --> 00:20:16,548
You know what?

334
00:20:17,007 --> 00:20:19,635
It was just for a while,
but I think we were pretty close.

335
00:20:20,886 --> 00:20:22,679
Why didn't you call me
before you took your leave?

336
00:20:23,180 --> 00:20:25,474
Was it because you became famous?

337
00:20:26,808 --> 00:20:28,018
I didn't like you guys.

338
00:20:31,897 --> 00:20:33,482
That's it for today.

339
00:20:33,565 --> 00:20:35,484
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

340
00:20:42,157 --> 00:20:44,117
-Let's go to eat.
-I'm on a diet.

341
00:20:55,504 --> 00:20:57,130
-That's it?
-Yes.

342
00:20:57,839 --> 00:21:00,884
But I just forgave her
because she got me her script.

343
00:21:01,718 --> 00:21:02,719
What?

344
00:21:04,054 --> 00:21:06,306
So-min got my script?

345
00:21:09,059 --> 00:21:10,894
Gosh, I don't like her.

346
00:21:11,103 --> 00:21:13,146
-What about Han-ju?
-Because she's prettier than me.

347
00:21:13,730 --> 00:21:15,232
But I just forgave her too.

348
00:21:15,315 --> 00:21:18,318
You just told me
that I'm the prettiest person you know.

349
00:21:34,751 --> 00:21:35,752
I think

350
00:21:36,795 --> 00:21:40,966
you're the prettiest person I know.

351
00:21:41,174 --> 00:21:42,301
That's true.

352
00:21:49,016 --> 00:21:50,100
Here.

353
00:21:53,395 --> 00:21:55,439
You too, Jin-joo. Here.

354
00:22:06,074 --> 00:22:08,535
-What about me?
-They only liked you.

355
00:22:09,494 --> 00:22:10,871
But I just forgave you

356
00:22:10,954 --> 00:22:13,165
because you said that Min-jun is amazing.

357
00:22:16,043 --> 00:22:17,252
That's very

358
00:22:18,170 --> 00:22:19,254
simple and lucid.

359
00:22:22,632 --> 00:22:25,886
So is that amazing guy doing well?

360
00:23:09,054 --> 00:23:11,223
You know you stand out
even more that way, don't you?

361
00:23:12,724 --> 00:23:14,476
Let's eat. I'll fix you a meal.

362
00:23:15,018 --> 00:23:17,229
Stay seated. I have something to do first.

363
00:23:18,355 --> 00:23:19,606
Hey.

364
00:23:33,995 --> 00:23:35,664
Damn it.

365
00:23:35,956 --> 00:23:38,250
Do you really have to say that
to someone who just kissed you?

366
00:23:39,417 --> 00:23:41,253
I told the agency that I'm going to quit.

367
00:23:41,711 --> 00:23:43,713
Okay. I'll just break your leg

368
00:23:43,797 --> 00:23:46,258
so you won't run away from me.
I'll feed you.

369
00:23:46,341 --> 00:23:48,552
I'm not going anywhere.
You don't have to break my leg.

370
00:23:49,636 --> 00:23:52,222
I'm going to Haenaem Entertainment.
I'll become successful.

371
00:23:52,305 --> 00:23:54,641
I'll make it to the CEO.
Just give me five years.

372
00:23:55,267 --> 00:23:57,769
What? Aren't you going
to see me for five years?

373
00:23:58,854 --> 00:23:59,896
Should I break your leg now?

374
00:23:59,980 --> 00:24:01,857
I can't live without you.

375
00:24:02,566 --> 00:24:03,942
Have you not realized it yet?

376
00:24:05,068 --> 00:24:06,153
I have.

377
00:24:07,445 --> 00:24:09,865
We will be working apart
and become very busy.

378
00:24:09,948 --> 00:24:12,993
But let's not be
understanding and considerate.

379
00:24:13,410 --> 00:24:14,703
We have to see each other every day.

380
00:24:14,953 --> 00:24:16,246
We have to meet even if we fight.

381
00:24:16,329 --> 00:24:17,914
We'll just grab each other by the collar.

382
00:24:18,331 --> 00:24:21,126
No, not the collar. Let's just...

383
00:24:22,419 --> 00:24:23,795
We will meet every day.

384
00:24:26,423 --> 00:24:27,465
Every day.

385
00:24:29,134 --> 00:24:31,011
Gee, this is awkward.

386
00:24:31,178 --> 00:24:32,429
Let me just cover your mouth.

387
00:26:35,635 --> 00:26:39,055
DOWNLOADED ITEMS

388
00:26:42,767 --> 00:26:44,561
-Can I come in?
-Yes.

389
00:27:02,454 --> 00:27:04,581
This isn't something that happens a lot.

390
00:27:05,957 --> 00:27:07,500
You're the only person I have.

391
00:27:09,002 --> 00:27:12,297
-What about Mun-su?
-Mun-su and you.

392
00:27:12,380 --> 00:27:13,631
What about Mom and Dad?

393
00:27:13,715 --> 00:27:16,468
Mom, Dad, Mun-su,

394
00:27:16,551 --> 00:27:18,678
-and you are all I have.
-What about In-guk?

395
00:27:19,387 --> 00:27:21,765
-Han-ju, Jin-joo--
-Enough.

396
00:27:25,643 --> 00:27:28,104
Just tell me what you want to say.
It's okay.

397
00:27:31,816 --> 00:27:33,735
One of A-rang's friends

398
00:27:34,444 --> 00:27:36,488
is a famous psychologist.

399
00:27:37,197 --> 00:27:40,200
She's been stressed out lately,
so she went to see her.

400
00:27:40,533 --> 00:27:41,618
And she found it nice.

401
00:27:42,702 --> 00:27:44,496
She recommended us to go there too.

402
00:28:15,443 --> 00:28:16,444
Okay.

403
00:28:18,071 --> 00:28:19,406
I get it.

404
00:28:20,740 --> 00:28:22,075
I'll go see her.

405
00:28:32,252 --> 00:28:33,753
Mr. Son, I'm here.

406
00:28:38,174 --> 00:28:39,592
The script was really fun.

407
00:28:39,676 --> 00:28:41,177
The writer is good.

408
00:28:41,261 --> 00:28:43,263
I should've come with So-yeon.

409
00:28:43,346 --> 00:28:45,807
But she just finished her project
and she's now abroad.

410
00:28:45,890 --> 00:28:48,017
I usually don't contact my actors
when they're on a break,

411
00:28:48,268 --> 00:28:51,062
but I liked the script so much
that I even e-mailed her right away.

412
00:28:51,146 --> 00:28:53,189
I told her to read it
and give me some feedback.

413
00:28:53,273 --> 00:28:54,649
We could've met after she finished it.

414
00:28:54,733 --> 00:28:57,777
It will take her a while though.
She has dyslexia.

415
00:28:58,778 --> 00:29:00,697
I heard she's starting a movie in July.

416
00:29:00,780 --> 00:29:02,115
It's not fixed. She's still thinking.

417
00:29:02,198 --> 00:29:05,243
I don't quite like it
because it's a supporting role,

418
00:29:05,326 --> 00:29:06,870
but the movie is large-scaled.

419
00:29:06,953 --> 00:29:08,872
And she likes to do movies.

420
00:29:08,955 --> 00:29:10,039
Then she might do it.

421
00:29:10,123 --> 00:29:11,332
But I want your project.

422
00:29:11,416 --> 00:29:12,959
Would So-yeon even listen to your agency?

423
00:29:13,042 --> 00:29:15,170
She'd listen. She will make
her own decision though.

424
00:29:15,253 --> 00:29:16,296
What are you talking about?

425
00:29:16,379 --> 00:29:17,922
It means she has good hearing.

426
00:29:19,799 --> 00:29:22,969
Oh, right. How about Lee So-min?

427
00:29:23,052 --> 00:29:25,013
-I knew you'd say that.
-I'm just saying

428
00:29:25,096 --> 00:29:27,307
in case you haven't thought about her.

429
00:29:27,390 --> 00:29:30,018
So-min is better when it comes to acting.

430
00:29:31,478 --> 00:29:33,480
-Has she got good reviews on her acting?
-Sure.

431
00:29:33,563 --> 00:29:34,856
-Where?
-Internally.

432
00:29:34,939 --> 00:29:36,274
You mean, in the agency?

433
00:29:36,524 --> 00:29:40,236
Come to think of it,
she will be perfect for this part.

434
00:29:40,320 --> 00:29:41,362
Is it your personal opinion?

435
00:29:41,446 --> 00:29:43,948
Just think about it.
I'll have her audition for the role.

436
00:29:44,032 --> 00:29:47,160
To be honest, she's too big to audition.

437
00:29:47,243 --> 00:29:49,496
Actually she's been working really hard.

438
00:29:49,579 --> 00:29:53,333
I even scolded her recently
to stop trying so hard.

439
00:30:08,890 --> 00:30:10,058
Hello, Ms. Hwang.

440
00:30:11,059 --> 00:30:12,894
We should have a meeting about casting.

441
00:30:13,728 --> 00:30:14,771
Right now.

442
00:30:15,772 --> 00:30:17,023
I'll see you at the office.

443
00:30:18,191 --> 00:30:19,442
Oh, right.

444
00:30:21,569 --> 00:30:23,112
Please call Ms. Lim too.

445
00:30:24,072 --> 00:30:26,115
How is Lee So-min doing
in the industry these days?

446
00:30:26,324 --> 00:30:28,660
She's hosting a talk show
on a cable TV channel.

447
00:30:28,743 --> 00:30:30,495
What was her latest drama?
I didn't watch it.

448
00:30:30,578 --> 00:30:32,539
Her last work was a weekend drama.

449
00:30:32,622 --> 00:30:36,251
It got pretty good ratings,
but it was a male lead-focused drama.

450
00:30:36,334 --> 00:30:38,419
So she's been on a downturn since then.

451
00:30:39,254 --> 00:30:41,214
I don't think
her acting skills are that bad.

452
00:30:41,506 --> 00:30:44,634
Mr. So sounded like he'd
give us Tae Min-gi for Jeong-gu.

453
00:30:45,385 --> 00:30:48,680
Tae Min-gi is a rising star.
I bet he might want the male lead.

454
00:30:48,763 --> 00:30:51,266
Apparently he's not sure
if he could pull off a sole male lead.

455
00:30:51,349 --> 00:30:52,392
By the way,

456
00:30:53,476 --> 00:30:54,561
where is Ms. Lim?

457
00:30:55,019 --> 00:30:57,522
She said she needs
to edit her script today.

458
00:30:59,065 --> 00:31:00,149
I mean,

459
00:31:01,526 --> 00:31:03,403
a casting meeting without the writer?

460
00:31:03,945 --> 00:31:07,156
She said she'd follow your opinions.

461
00:31:09,617 --> 00:31:11,536
Should we try contacting other agencies?

462
00:31:11,619 --> 00:31:13,913
If you could just
narrow down the candidates...

463
00:31:15,373 --> 00:31:18,084
Let me watch some
of Lee So-min's dramas first.

464
00:31:18,501 --> 00:31:19,502
Excuse me.

465
00:31:19,961 --> 00:31:20,962
Hello?

466
00:31:22,213 --> 00:31:23,381
What are you doing this evening?

467
00:31:23,590 --> 00:31:25,508
-Let's hang out.
-Are you lonely?

468
00:31:26,593 --> 00:31:27,719
Hang out with Dong-gi.

469
00:31:27,802 --> 00:31:32,056
I want to have a drink
with Hwan-dong, Ms. Jung, and Ms. Lim.

470
00:31:32,515 --> 00:31:35,977
Isn't it nice? We don't have to feel
uncomfortable around each other.

471
00:31:36,060 --> 00:31:37,478
We are uncomfortable around each other.

472
00:31:38,354 --> 00:31:39,480
No.

473
00:31:40,648 --> 00:31:43,776
Fine. Then can you call Ms. Lim?

474
00:31:43,860 --> 00:31:45,778
Me? Why?

475
00:31:45,862 --> 00:31:48,323
She might nag me
for doing something useless.

476
00:31:49,782 --> 00:31:52,327
I'm in a meeting now,
so text me where to meet up.

477
00:31:58,458 --> 00:32:01,336
Gosh, why is it so hard
not seeing her? It's just one day.

478
00:32:08,009 --> 00:32:10,178
I made seaweed soup for you.

479
00:32:10,261 --> 00:32:12,555
-But you just put noodles in it?
-It's delicious.

480
00:32:15,224 --> 00:32:17,560
And why would you come here to work
when you have your own office?

481
00:32:17,644 --> 00:32:18,937
I feel lonely.

482
00:32:20,521 --> 00:32:21,981
You sound spoiled.

483
00:32:22,607 --> 00:32:24,484
I become hungry when I skip a meal.

484
00:32:24,567 --> 00:32:26,319
And I become lonely when I'm full.

485
00:32:26,402 --> 00:32:27,946
I guess that's life.

486
00:32:32,825 --> 00:32:34,535
I've learned a lot from you, ma'am.

487
00:32:47,298 --> 00:32:50,176
Come to the sashimi restaurant near
the broadcasting station by seven tonight.

488
00:32:50,259 --> 00:32:51,552
Let's have dinner and drinks.

489
00:32:53,054 --> 00:32:54,347
What is this?

490
00:32:54,847 --> 00:32:55,848
Why?

491
00:33:00,311 --> 00:33:02,146
I'm going out to have dinner again.

492
00:33:04,524 --> 00:33:07,068
-I should get going.
-See you.

493
00:33:13,074 --> 00:33:16,494
Jae-hun. Aren't you supposed
to watch the musical tonight?

494
00:33:18,204 --> 00:33:19,455
That's right.

495
00:33:19,539 --> 00:33:21,708
You should hurry.
There might be a traffic jam.

496
00:33:22,125 --> 00:33:23,126
Okay.

497
00:33:23,793 --> 00:33:25,169
Aren't you getting off?

498
00:33:25,628 --> 00:33:27,547
Just wrap things up and go first.

499
00:33:31,926 --> 00:33:34,429
I'll be off then.

500
00:33:36,764 --> 00:33:37,974
Have fun on your date.

501
00:33:39,100 --> 00:33:40,101
Okay.

502
00:33:48,443 --> 00:33:51,154
I broke up with her. It's been a few days.

503
00:33:53,448 --> 00:33:54,574
Will you...

504
00:33:58,036 --> 00:33:59,662
watch it with me?

505
00:34:04,333 --> 00:34:06,794
I need to go pick In-guk up.

506
00:34:08,796 --> 00:34:11,215
-Hang on a second.
-No, it's fine then.

507
00:34:11,299 --> 00:34:13,134
No. Just a moment.

508
00:34:20,224 --> 00:34:22,894
Hey, Hyo-bong. I love you.

509
00:34:22,977 --> 00:34:26,105
-Okay.
-Okay, I love you.

510
00:34:29,233 --> 00:34:30,234
Let's go.

511
00:35:00,807 --> 00:35:02,266
Ms. Lim, we're here.

512
00:35:23,913 --> 00:35:24,789
That's right.

513
00:35:24,872 --> 00:35:27,083
A director and a writer should
sit across from each other.

514
00:35:27,166 --> 00:35:29,293
