782
00:51:35,050 --> 00:51:36,218
Selling the drama overseas?

783
00:51:37,135 --> 00:51:38,261
The second season?

784
00:51:39,054 --> 00:51:40,055
Me.

785
00:51:43,642 --> 00:51:45,602
My feelings for you.

786
00:51:47,604 --> 00:51:49,231
It's not just that I like you.

787
00:51:53,485 --> 00:51:54,986
I like you so much

788
00:52:00,075 --> 00:52:01,284
that I need you to do something.

789
00:52:13,505 --> 00:52:17,676
We both found out about our feelings
that we'd been trying to hide.

790
00:52:18,510 --> 00:52:21,555
And we both knew our feelings
that we'd implicitly been hiding

791
00:52:21,847 --> 00:52:24,140
would eventually come out.

792
00:52:25,433 --> 00:52:27,143
But neither of us knew

793
00:52:28,562 --> 00:52:29,771
that it'd happen today.

794
00:52:36,236 --> 00:52:37,737
Come in.

795
00:52:45,704 --> 00:52:46,997
Hello.

796
00:52:47,205 --> 00:52:48,290
Hello.

797
00:52:49,291 --> 00:52:51,001
Nice to meet you. Come sit over here.

798
00:52:57,257 --> 00:53:00,093
Have you been to a place like this before?

799
00:53:00,302 --> 00:53:01,553
Or met a psychologist?

800
00:53:01,720 --> 00:53:04,389
No, this is my first time.

801
00:53:05,724 --> 00:53:06,725
How do you feel?

802
00:53:07,601 --> 00:53:08,685
It feels cozy.

803
00:53:09,477 --> 00:53:12,439
I thought what I saw
in movies was made up.

804
00:53:12,731 --> 00:53:15,317
Some are from the movies,
and some are my taste.

805
00:53:15,817 --> 00:53:16,818
It's nice.

806
00:53:17,611 --> 00:53:19,946
Normally, I'd give you a questionnaire

807
00:53:20,030 --> 00:53:22,949
and review your answers
before talking to you.

808
00:53:23,491 --> 00:53:24,826
But let's just talk.

809
00:53:25,702 --> 00:53:28,371
A-rang told me a lot about you,
so I can't pretend not to know you.

810
00:53:28,580 --> 00:53:30,248
It would feel like lying.

811
00:53:30,332 --> 00:53:32,417
What do you normally start talking about?

812
00:53:32,500 --> 00:53:35,086
I ask about your job,
your family background,

813
00:53:35,253 --> 00:53:37,088
and whether or not you drink or smoke.

814
00:53:37,797 --> 00:53:41,509
And most importantly,
I ask you what I'm curious about.

815
00:53:43,053 --> 00:53:43,887
Okay.

816
00:53:43,970 --> 00:53:46,014
I'll just ask you
things that come to my mind.

817
00:53:46,139 --> 00:53:48,266
You don't need to answer
if you feel uncomfortable.

818
00:53:52,270 --> 00:53:55,649
When you watch a sad movie
or feel like crying,

819
00:53:56,316 --> 00:53:58,276
are you easily moved to tears?

820
00:53:59,486 --> 00:54:01,613
When was the last time you shed tears?

821
00:54:06,076 --> 00:54:07,786
You may take your time.

822
00:54:13,208 --> 00:54:14,334
Tears...

823
00:54:19,422 --> 00:54:20,674
I don't remember.

824
00:54:24,511 --> 00:54:26,221
It's been more than two years.

825
00:54:31,726 --> 00:54:33,103
It was hard.

826
00:54:35,313 --> 00:54:38,608
His parents visited him
at the hospital only once.

827
00:54:45,949 --> 00:54:49,369
I didn't leave his side even for a moment.

828
00:54:51,538 --> 00:54:53,289
He was in pain,

829
00:54:54,457 --> 00:54:58,753
but fortunately, he didn't
hide himself until the end.

830
00:55:02,007 --> 00:55:03,925
He didn't push me away.

831
00:55:07,595 --> 00:55:09,139
I'm grateful for it.

832
00:55:20,817 --> 00:55:23,194
He was unconscious for a long time.

833
00:55:25,405 --> 00:55:26,740
One night,

834
00:55:28,825 --> 00:55:30,785
he woke me up.

835
00:55:32,454 --> 00:55:34,372
He couldn't even talk,

836
00:55:36,166 --> 00:55:38,334
but his eyes seemed so peaceful.

837
00:55:40,503 --> 00:55:43,673
I could understand
what he was trying to say at once.

838
00:56:05,737 --> 00:56:08,740
He passed away by my side. That night.

839
00:56:13,661 --> 00:56:14,746
And...

840
00:56:37,352 --> 00:56:38,853
And I don't remember.

841
00:56:41,898 --> 00:56:42,899
Actually,

842
00:56:44,776 --> 00:56:46,820
I don't think I've ever cried since then.

843
00:56:48,363 --> 00:56:51,366
I feel like I have no feelings.

844
00:56:52,283 --> 00:56:53,785
How do you feel these days?

845
00:56:56,371 --> 00:56:57,622
It's bearable.

846
00:56:57,831 --> 00:56:59,249
What do you mean by bearable?

847
00:57:00,500 --> 00:57:03,711
Well... I'm doing a hard job.

848
00:57:03,795 --> 00:57:05,255
It'd be strange

849
00:57:06,005 --> 00:57:08,174
if it wasn't hard to make a documentary.

850
00:57:08,800 --> 00:57:10,218
It's just okay.

851
00:57:11,678 --> 00:57:12,679
I'm glad to hear that.

852
00:57:12,762 --> 00:57:15,473
Then let's put your work aside.

853
00:57:16,141 --> 00:57:17,892
Besides your work,

854
00:57:17,976 --> 00:57:19,644
how do you usually feel?

855
00:57:26,317 --> 00:57:27,861
I didn't know well.

856
00:57:28,820 --> 00:57:31,656
I wasn't aware of my feelings.

857
00:57:32,282 --> 00:57:33,533
But one day,

858
00:57:35,285 --> 00:57:38,705
I felt like something
that makes me feel emotions

859
00:57:38,788 --> 00:57:41,666
was stuck on the ground.

860
00:57:42,625 --> 00:57:44,419
I tried to take it off,

861
00:57:45,044 --> 00:57:48,173
but it didn't even budge as if

862
00:57:48,256 --> 00:57:49,507
it had been always there.

863
00:57:49,757 --> 00:57:52,969
I think that's a positive signal
at least for you.

864
00:57:53,428 --> 00:57:55,388
-What?
-Actually,

865
00:57:55,805 --> 00:57:59,350
it's an emotion
that depressed people feel.

866
00:57:59,559 --> 00:58:01,436
But it's like

867
00:58:01,769 --> 00:58:04,314
you found yourself back
from your big trauma

868
00:58:04,397 --> 00:58:06,524
which had made you
unable to recognize yourself.

869
00:58:06,858 --> 00:58:10,403
I believe there's some
positive element around you.

870
00:58:11,279 --> 00:58:13,656
My friends are always there for me.

871
00:58:15,617 --> 00:58:18,995
We eat, drink, and talk together

872
00:58:19,412 --> 00:58:20,705
every single day.

873
00:58:21,831 --> 00:58:25,335
Girls would fight a lot
when they live together,

874
00:58:25,627 --> 00:58:28,671
but we are not like that. I like it.

875
00:58:29,672 --> 00:58:32,509
I envy you. They are such good friends.

876
00:58:33,176 --> 00:58:35,053
How is your relationship
with your parents?

877
00:58:35,136 --> 00:58:36,596
They live abroad.

878
00:58:37,055 --> 00:58:40,475
-I just call them from time to time.
-I see.

879
00:58:41,100 --> 00:58:43,520
Isn't there any problem
with your relationship?

880
00:58:43,603 --> 00:58:44,604
No.

881
00:58:47,023 --> 00:58:50,985
I know that they had a hard time
because of my brother,

882
00:58:52,987 --> 00:58:54,531
but I think

883
00:58:56,241 --> 00:58:57,825
they've done

884
00:58:57,909 --> 00:59:00,036
as much as they could.

885
00:59:01,454 --> 00:59:03,498
What about your childhood memories?

886
00:59:06,084 --> 00:59:07,835
We had no problems.

887
00:59:08,211 --> 00:59:10,672
Is there any memory
that comes to your mind

888
00:59:10,755 --> 00:59:12,674
when you think of
your childhood with them?

889
00:59:12,924 --> 00:59:14,092
Just anything.

890
00:59:14,676 --> 00:59:17,804
When you got scolded or felt happy.

891
00:59:20,682 --> 00:59:22,100
It's nothing special,

892
00:59:22,475 --> 00:59:25,687
but my mom was working back then.

893
00:59:26,729 --> 00:59:27,981
So I hardly have

894
00:59:28,773 --> 00:59:31,818
any memory of spending time with her
on weekdays.

895
00:59:32,902 --> 00:59:36,447
But that day, she didn't
go to work for some reason.

896
00:59:36,573 --> 00:59:38,908
I was about 10.

897
00:59:39,033 --> 00:59:41,077
It was the school anniversary,
so I was at home.

898
00:59:42,662 --> 00:59:45,123
She talked less than usual.

899
00:59:45,665 --> 00:59:49,460
I wondered why and studied her feelings.

900
00:59:52,005 --> 00:59:55,508
She asked me
what I wanted to eat for lunch.

901
00:59:55,967 --> 00:59:57,093
I said cotton candy.

902
00:59:59,304 --> 01:00:02,265
There was a small park with a few rides

903
01:00:02,348 --> 01:00:04,142
in the neighborhood.

904
01:00:04,350 --> 01:00:07,145
We weren't well off at that time,

905
01:00:07,228 --> 01:00:09,480
so we couldn't afford to go there often.

906
01:00:09,772 --> 01:00:12,400
She took me to the park

907
01:00:12,483 --> 01:00:14,611
without saying anything.

908
01:00:15,695 --> 01:00:17,864
I ate a hamburger.

909
01:00:18,156 --> 01:00:19,949
And I ate cotton candy.

910
01:00:34,881 --> 01:00:37,634
I rode a ride that cost 3,000 won.

911
01:00:38,092 --> 01:00:40,053
I was supposed to be excited.

912
01:00:40,803 --> 01:00:44,807
But looking at my mom
sitting on a bench vacantly,

913
01:00:45,725 --> 01:00:50,146
I was concerned about her
even though I was young.

914
01:00:51,105 --> 01:00:54,150
So I just sat

915
01:00:54,901 --> 01:00:57,236
next to her for a while.

916
01:00:57,695 --> 01:01:00,907
What happened to her?

917
01:01:02,784 --> 01:01:04,035
I have no idea.

918
01:01:07,997 --> 01:01:09,582
Why do you think she did that?

919
01:01:11,876 --> 01:01:13,211
I never asked her why.

920
01:01:15,546 --> 01:01:16,923
If I ask her now,

921
01:01:18,508 --> 01:01:20,802
she might not even remember it.

922
01:01:22,929 --> 01:01:23,971
The day

923
01:01:26,599 --> 01:01:28,768
just passed by like that.

924
01:01:29,769 --> 01:01:31,604
Why do you think you recalled that day?

925
01:01:32,814 --> 01:01:34,023
I don't know.

926
01:01:36,109 --> 01:01:37,777
It's not something

927
01:01:38,194 --> 01:01:41,114
that I tried to remember.

928
01:01:43,658 --> 01:01:44,742
I just...

929
01:01:49,038 --> 01:01:50,790
don't know.

930
01:02:23,614 --> 01:02:24,866
I'm sorry.

931
01:02:32,457 --> 01:02:34,083
It's okay. It's no problem.

932
01:02:54,437 --> 01:02:57,774
What happened between you and her?

933
01:03:05,823 --> 01:03:09,076
WE WILL BE WORKING APART
AND BECOME VERY BUSY

934
01:03:09,160 --> 01:03:13,289
BUT LET'S NOT BE UNDERSTANDING

935
01:03:13,372 --> 01:03:14,999
AND CONSIDERATE

936
01:03:15,082 --> 01:03:17,251
WE HAVE TO SEE EACH OTHER EVERY DAY

937
01:03:19,378 --> 01:03:23,049
TWO HEDGEHOGS ARE WANDERING
AROUND IN A COMPLICATED MAZE

938
01:03:23,132 --> 01:03:25,218
THEY KEEP POKING EACH OTHER

939
01:03:25,301 --> 01:03:27,970
AND THEY BOTH END UP BLEEDING SO MUCH

940
01:03:28,054 --> 01:03:30,097
AT SOME POINT, THEY CAN'T STAND IT ANYMORE

941
01:03:30,181 --> 01:03:34,060
AND SET THE MAZE ON FIRE AND RUN AWAY

942
01:03:34,143 --> 01:03:38,272
THE SPACE THEY SHARED IS GONE

943
01:03:38,356 --> 01:03:41,692
THEN I OPEN MY EYES,
AND I DON'T KNOW WHERE I AM ANYMORE

944
01:03:43,027 --> 01:03:45,279
MY FEELINGS FOR YOU

945
01:03:45,363 --> 01:03:47,990
IT'S NOT JUST THAT I LIKE YOU

946
01:03:48,074 --> 01:03:51,035
I LIKE YOU SO MUCH

947
01:03:51,118 --> 01:03:53,955
THAT I NEED YOU TO DO SOMETHING

948
01:03:56,290 --> 01:03:58,793
What about Ha-yun?
I feel thrilled when I break up.

949
01:03:58,876 --> 01:04:00,545
It's not the end, but a new beginning.

950
01:04:00,628 --> 01:04:03,047
You can text me
if you're depressed at home.

951
01:04:03,130 --> 01:04:04,131
I'll wait.

952
01:04:04,215 --> 01:04:05,091
Are you glad to see me?

953
01:04:05,174 --> 01:04:06,342
Are you seeing someone?

954
01:04:06,425 --> 01:04:08,219
She has a kid. Is that okay?

955
01:04:08,553 --> 01:04:09,971
Can you help me up?

956
01:04:10,054 --> 01:04:11,722
Just stay there!

957
01:04:11,806 --> 01:04:13,933
Why do you say I'm not here?
Do you not need me anymore?

958
01:04:14,016 --> 01:04:16,269
-Die.
-I'm going to kill you!

959
01:04:17,103 --> 01:04:18,729
We already like each other.

960
01:04:18,813 --> 01:04:19,647
On hold.

961
01:04:19,730 --> 01:04:21,274
Do you have time tonight?

962
01:04:21,357 --> 01:04:23,985
I wanted to have dinner like this
with you just once.

963
01:04:24,068 --> 01:04:26,445
I guess you've never lost someone
you like without doing anything.

964
01:04:26,529 --> 01:04:28,573
but you need to know
how nerve-wracking it is.

965
01:04:28,656 --> 01:04:30,783
Mr. Son, what is love?

966
01:04:30,867 --> 01:04:32,410
We had definitely become different.

967
01:04:32,493 --> 01:04:34,161
The best thing in this world.

968
01:04:35,371 --> 01:04:37,415
